children.subject: Seniors graduating in Fall 2016 have priority. I believe all other LSCS students are considered equal.

Seniors graduating in the same semester will always receive priority for a class required for their major. A small number of seats were also given to CS seniors graduating in Spring 2017. The faculty are prioritizing CS-intended incoming freshmen. Sophomores and juniors do not have priority.
Will L&S CS sophomores and juniors ever get priority in the future?

Another question: for EE16a, which of these is the correct priority order for LSCS?

senior > junior > sophomore > freshman > undeclared anything

freshman > sophomore > junior > senior > undeclared anything

history.content:
Lydia is the EE Scheduler who monitors this waitlist and is out of the office today, but I will do my best to answer. 


Right now, seats are reserved for incoming EECS freshmen or junior transfers, who are encouraged to take the course during their first semester. Seats are also reserved for LSCS seniors who need the course for Fall graduation. There are additional less-relevant enrollment categories. After phase II, any unused seats will be released. These will mostly be the seats reserved for incoming EECS students who elect not to take the course this semester. Unfortunately we will not know how many until closer to the time. 

To add to Nicole's post, we are also reserving seats for incoming CS-intended freshmen until Aug 15. Any unused seat will be released on Aug 15 and the waitlist will be processed in order. Unfortunately, it's really hard for us to know how many reserved seats will open up right now. We will probably have more information for you after CalSO since that's when the incoming freshmen will enroll in classes.
